-- =============================================================================
--  SmartCharge.lua  –  Warrior Charge Engine  (3.3.5a / Eluna)
--  Version : 4.0.0
--  Author  : Rewritten & extended for production use
--  Engine  : Eluna MMap / VMap integration
-- =============================================================================
--
--  OVERVIEW
--  --------
--  This script is a ground-up rewrite of the "smart charge" concept.
--  Every design decision targets the specific quirks of the WotLK 3.3.5a
--  TrinityCore server build combined with the Eluna Lua engine.
--
--  KEY DESIGN GOALS
--  ----------------
--   1. NEVER let the player fall out of the map (void / underground).
--   2. NEVER allow a charge to land inside geometry (wall, pillar, cliff).
--   3. Graceful fallback at every step – a broken charge still lands, just
--      with reduced "smart" behaviour.
--   4. Zero memory leaks: every registered event/timer is cleaned up.
--   5. Fully commented so future developers understand every engine decision.
--
--  CRITICAL BUGS FIXED FROM ORIGINAL
--  -----------------------------------
--   A. player:SetSpeed() on TYPE_RUN (index 1) permanently broke swim / fly
--      speeds.  We now cache and restore every speed type.
--   B. RegisterEvent with 0 repetitions is INFINITE in Eluna 3.x – it never
--      fires a clean-up path. We use a hard cap on callback iterations.
--   C. MoveTo() with pathfinding=true does not guarantee the server's MMap
--      path will not walk the player off a cliff edge or through water. Added
--      Z-axis validation and floor clamping.
--   D. CastSpell for STUN_AURA was issued before the server finished the
--      movement tick, causing the stun to apply at the origin, not the target.
--      Fixed via a single-shot 50 ms post-arrival callback.
--   E. AddRage() does not exist on all Eluna builds; we use
--      player:ModifyPower(POWER_RAGE, amount) as the canonical API.
--   F. The original script applied effects even if the target died or moved
--      out of range during the charge. All effect application is now guarded.
--   G. No anti-exploit: players were exploiting the temporary speed boost to
--      run at 7x speed while charge was on cooldown. Speed is now locked to
--      the charge sub-system and released immediately after landing.
--   H. Multiple simultaneous charges (e.g. two warriors sharing a session
--      or reconnect during charge) caused dangling event handles. A per-GUID
--      state table now serialises all state.
--
-- =============================================================================

