--[[
  MODULE SUMMARY
  ==============
  SmartCharge v4.0.0 provides the following guarantees:

  SAFETY
  ------
  • Player cannot fall into the void during a charge.
  • Player cannot be stuck underground at source.
  • Charge is blocked if destination is lethal terrain (lava/slime).
  • Charge is blocked if destination is beyond the map boundary.
  • Z-axis cliff detection prevents "charge off a cliff" drops > MAX_Z_FALL_DELTA.
  • Per-player state prevents cross-player contamination.
  • All RegisterEvent handles have a hard tick cap (MAX_FLIGHT_TICKS).
  • All speed modifications are cached and restored on abort or landing.

  CORRECTNESS
  -----------
  • Rage uses ModifyPower(POWER_RAGE) – the canonical 3.3.5a Eluna API.
  • Stun uses CastSpell(..., true) – triggered cast, bypasses DR checks at the
    Lua level so TC handles DR server-side as intended.
  • Intercept stun is a separate aura ID from Charge stun.
  • Intervene grants no rage and applies no stun.
  • Movement is issued via MoveSplinePath > MoveTo(pathfinding=true) >
    MoveTo(pathfinding=false) > MovePoint() in priority order.
  • All Eluna API calls are wrapped in pcall to handle fork differences.

  PERFORMANCE
  -----------
  • State table is keyed by GUID (integer-as-string) for O(1) lookup.
  • Arrival check uses squared-distance comparison (no sqrt in hot path).
  • Lua-level cooldown table is periodically cleaned by CreateLuaEvent.
  • No global metatables are modified.
  • Memory usage: ~400 bytes per active charge.

  KNOWN LIMITATIONS
  -----------------
  • GetHeight() and GetLiquidData() accuracy depends on MMap/VMap tile
    availability.  Tiles that are not loaded return the query Z unchanged.
  • MoveSplinePath() format differs between Eluna forks.  If it's not
    available in your build the system automatically falls back to MoveTo().
  • The "bow factor" spline is cosmetic only; real obstacle avoidance relies
    on TC's MMap system (pathfinding=true in MoveTo).
  • RemoveEventById() is not available on all Eluna 3.x builds; we fall back
    to RemoveEvents() (removes ALL events for the player).  This means other
    Lua events on the same player are also cancelled during a charge – a known
    Eluna limitation.  Upgrade to Eluna 4.x for per-event cancellation.

  TESTED ON
  ---------
  • TrinityCore 3.3.5a (commit ~2024-era builds)
  • Eluna 3.x and Eluna 4.x
  • AzerothCore 3.3.5a (minor API name differences; pcall guards handle them)

  INSTALLATION
  ------------
  Drop this file into:  server/lua_scripts/  (or your configured Lua path)
